[{"id":27626,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["A and D only","A,B and E only","B,C and E only","B and E only"],"answer":3,"solution":"(A) $\\mathrm{R}-\\mathrm{C} \\equiv \\mathrm{N} \\xrightarrow[\\text { mild condition }]{\\text { (i) } \\mathrm{H}^{+} / \\mathrm{H}_2 \\mathrm{O}} \\mathrm{R}-\\mathrm{CONH}_2$<br />Under mild condition amide is formed because this reaction is typically slow if further more heat will supplied then it gets convert in to -COOH.<br />(B) $\\mathrm{R}-\\mathrm{MgX} \\xrightarrow[\\text { (ii) } \\mathrm{H}_3 \\mathrm{O}^{+}]{\\text {(i) } \\mathrm{CO}_2} \\mathrm{R}-\\mathrm{COOH}$<br />(C) $\\mathrm{R}-\\mathrm{C} \\equiv \\mathrm{N} \\xrightarrow[\\text { (ii) } \\mathrm{H}_3 \\mathrm{O}^{+}]{\\text {(i) } \\mathrm{SnCl}_2 / \\mathrm{HCl}} \\mathrm{R}-\\mathrm{CHO}$<br />(D) $\\mathrm{R} \\cdot \\mathrm{CH}_2 \\cdot \\mathrm{OH} \\xrightarrow{\\mathrm{PCC}} \\mathrm{R}-\\mathrm{CHO}$<br />(E) <br /><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/TBqlwFTjkSIABCdcP63HxkIiWKpYn9w9mCCbj3TBRoU.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (2 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27669,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/5df8221c-3249-4529-8ad1-88b27a95ea61-image.png\" style=\"width: 169px; height: 191px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/d252b9e2-d1a6-41c5-aecd-4a1d01cd3831-image.png\" style=\"width: 220px; height: 168px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/9f1771c2-1830-416b-9fc1-543fc7713766-image.png\" style=\"width: 198px; height: 193px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/c28d38bc-edae-48c6-91f9-405c656c945f-image.png\" style=\"width: 198px; height: 165px;\" />"],"answer":0,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/fa24b981-1e51-464a-91f4-ca9a8105a734-image26.png\" style=\"width: 500px; height: 149px;\" /><br /><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/29c89